  "description": "Prosody is the study and practice of the sound patterns in verse: [meter](./meter.md), rhythm, [rhyme](./rhyme.md), stress, intonation, and the way these interact with meaning. It is the technical discipline of understanding how a poem sounds and why it sounds that way.",
